verbose_text: The remaining 17 studies / analyses showed a decreased-risk of PCa after comparing high vs. low levels of testosterone [XREF_FIG (numbers 5-9,11, 13, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19 and 20-25) and XREF_TABLE], but only 11 were statistically significant [XREF_FIG (numbers 6-9,13, 16, 17, 18, 20, 21, 25) and XREF_TABLE].
